  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nDue to the Active Validator Count Cache being introduced in #6254, this unfortunately leads\r\nto invalid genesis states in restarts. The cache stores a single value for a fixed seed, however\r\nin genesis when we have constant stream of genesis deposits coming in, this stored value will more than often be wrong. The seed doesn't change but the active count does. \r\n\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nYes before #6254 \r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nRun a node with an empty db and sync a few deposits before the `min_genesis_validator` count. Then restart the node, after a while the node will not derive the correct genesis state. \r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\nIncorrect active validator count derived from the cache leads to incorrect genesis event being determined.\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\nUbunutu 18.04.4 LTS\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n4740f7ed57490a5a38601a1e66cb8a66f0a6df50\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\n\r\n",
